WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.560
To use the application is very easy, so this is the initial display of

00:00:03.560 --> 00:00:08.520
the application, let's zoom in, you can click here to open

00:00:08.520 --> 00:00:11.600
the file, and what I like is that the layout is adaptive,

00:00:11.680 --> 00:00:15.260
so for example if I choose a video like this,

00:00:15.340 --> 00:00:19.560
16:9 then the layout looks like this, but if I use a format that

00:00:19.560 --> 00:00:23.640
is vertical, like in Shorts or Reels, the layout will adapt like this,

00:00:23.780 --> 00:00:28.540
and this can also be adjusted for length and width. Here we have

00:00:28.540 --> 00:00:33.200
several sections, the main one being the detection section,

00:00:33.460 --> 00:00:37.020
so this is the sound wave, this is the unedited video,

00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:41.480
there are many empty sections like this, this can be zoomed in,

00:00:41.860 --> 00:00:45.280
zooming out, you can see there are many empty sections,

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:49.640
we can go straight to detect, there are also several presets available,

00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:52.780
I'll just select default, then select detect silence,

00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:58.580
after a while, these segments will appear. We can

00:00:58.580 --> 00:01:01.940
zoom in, we can see there are silent sections,

00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:05.820
there's silence here, there's silence here, and the threshold can be adjusted

00:01:05.820 --> 00:01:09.540
of course, here the silence sections are. This can be shifted to

00:01:09.740 --> 00:01:12.620
view the whole thing, and it's quite accurate,

00:01:12.960 --> 00:01:15.620
if you want to edit, you can just click here,

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:19.880
the edit section, can be edited, or removed,

00:01:19.980 --> 00:01:24.420
the unsuitable parts. And here you can see, the resulting video duration

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:29.100
is 23 minutes, if we render, we export,

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:34.200
that's 8 minutes total, after cutting. And if we want to cut

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:38.420
part of it, we can take just a part, here if we don't want to

00:01:38.420 --> 00:01:42.440
take the entire video, just a specific part,

00:01:42.580 --> 00:01:46.260
this is possible. For example, I want to take from

00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:50.900
minute 0 to minute 1.46, the estimated result is

00:01:50.900 --> 00:01:55.800
58 seconds. That's because the empty parts have been removed,

00:01:55.880 --> 00:01:58.460
the empty sections. Okay, let's try

00:01:58.700 --> 00:02:03.400
cutting. I'll just use this one,

00:02:03.660 --> 00:02:08.419
replace, okay. And this will start the rendering process. And here

00:02:08.419 --> 00:02:12.700
you can see, the result matches, 58 seconds, and here 58 seconds.

00:02:13.060 --> 00:02:18.040
The result can be checked later. Of course, we can also preview here,

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:22.220
press space. So this button's function is to jump,

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:25.580
or jump. So basically this button is to simulate

00:02:26.140 --> 00:02:29.920
how each segment will look before rendering. Although not perfect

00:02:29.920 --> 00:02:33.880
for now, but I'll try to improve it. And that's how

00:02:33.940 --> 00:02:37.760
to use the software. And if there are questions, criticism or suggestions,

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:41.460
or feature requests, you can go to the contact section, we can discuss there.

00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:42.740
Thank you, see you next time.